{
  "texts": [
    "The agents can also receive local rewards, with designs to make the reward depend on teammates' collective performance [41, 48, 49, 80-82, 86, 87, 90], to penalize collisions [38, 80-82, 85, 89, 91, 92], or to share the reward with other agents for encouraging mutual cooperation [64,83,84].There are a variety of cooperative environments where communication has shown performance improvements, from small-scale games to complex video games.",
    "In early works, Foerster et al. [72] developed two simple games, named Switch Riddle and MNIST Games, for their proposed models, DIAL and RIAL.",
    "Sukhbaatar et al. [47] used Traffic Junction for evaluating CommNet, which has become a popular testbed in recent works [48,78,82,[87][88][89]91].",
    "Among them, MAGIC [91] achieved higher performance on Traffic Junction with local rewards compared to two early works, CommNet [47], IC3Net [48], and one recent work, GA-Comm [82].",
    "StarCraft [95][96][97] is another benchmark environment in cooperative MARL with relatively flexible settings."
  ]
}